spanishExample: ¿Lo puedes buscar mientras yo llevo a los chicos ahí?
englishTranslation: Can you look for it while I take the kids there?

spanishExample: ¿Puedes llevar estos dieciocho libros a tu casa?
englishTranslation: Can you take these eighteen books to your house?

spanishExample: Diecisiete es la mitad del largo que necesitas.
englishTranslation: Seventeen is half of the length you need.
These things are yet to come.

spanishExample: La media de esta semana es dieciocho o diecinueve.
englishTranslation: This week’s average is eighteen or nineteen.

spanishExample: Lleva eso para allá, no lo estamos tomando.
englishTranslation: Take that over there, we’re not drinking it.

spanishExample: Llevaré esas dieciséis cosas a otro lado.
englishTranslation: I’ll take those sixteen things to another place.

spanishExample: Llevó a los diecinueve chicos a la escuela.
englishTranslation: He took the nineteen kids to school.

spanishExample: Quieren que tome lo que él tomó.
englishTranslation: They want me to drink what he drank.

spanishExample: Quiero que tome lo que quiera tomar.
englishTranslation: I want him to drink whatever he wants to drink.

spanishExample: Siempre llevas la misma ropa que ella lleva.
englishTranslation: You always wear the same clothes she’s wearing.

spanishExample: Todo está en orden, no tienes que volverte loco.
englishTranslation: Everything is in order, you don’t have to go crazy.

spanishExample: Toma café mientras yo los estoy buscando.
englishTranslation: He drinks coffee while I’m looking for them.

spanishExample: Toma esto, ya no lo necesito porque él vuelve a las dos y media.
englishTranslation: Take this; I don’t need it anymore because he comes back at half past two.

spanishExample: Tuvimos una baja esa semana y ahora hay solo dieciséis personas.
englishTranslation: We had a drop that week and now there are only sixteen people.
We’re going to come back soon.

spanishExample: Van a llegar en diecisiete minutos.
englishTranslation: They are going to arrive in seventeen minutes.
